latestIgtvVideos.caption:
WORK ON YOUR BACKBENDS (with variations in the same pose) 
LIKE & SAVE for for later 🏷 ..
.
FOR ALL LEVELS! ⚡️
Work on your backbends from variations in one pose: Cobra Pose/ Bhujangasana.
My back feels great after these. Hope to see you guys trying it out and share how it was for you. .
.
Listen to your body and end with rounding the spine in Child’s Pose!
Make sure you inhale while lifting up, take at least 5 long breaths while in the pose and exhale while coming down

latestIgtvVideos.title: Happy Yoga Day : Variations in Chrarasana/Urdha Dhanurasana/Wheel Pose
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
It has been a few years now since this day was recognised as the international day of Yoga. Important things deserve recognition and trust me when I say that there is no substitute for Yoga especially during these times. 
A few weeks ago, everyone in my house were down with covid-19. How everyone caught it was like a domino effect. It was/is surprising when I was the only one that tested negative and I had been in contact with contaminated surfaces for sure. I don’t know how this virus works but I’ll owe at least a little to knowing how to breathe correctly and having stronger lungs or immunity. I personally owe it all to my practice. 
All extension postures, balancing postures, controlled breathing in the postures, Abdominal breathing, Kapalbhaati, Pranayamas like - Alternate nostril breathing, Ujjayi and Bhramri work like magic. 🌼

So, to the importance of this day- hope something clicks in you to at least give it a shot if you haven’t and improve your practice if you have. 💫 Stay humble, stay mindful and stay healthy. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

latestPosts.caption:
On this International Women’s Day, I celebrate not just my journey but the limitless potential within every woman. As a yoga teacher and mental health professional, I’ve broken through societal barriers to embrace a path that truly fulfills my spirit. 

When I made the leap from a conventional career to the mat, I discovered my passion for guiding others on their own journeys of self-discovery and healing. I remember the first time a student told me that my class had helped her find peace amidst chaos—my heart swelled with joy, knowing I was making a difference. 

Every time I step onto the mat, I remind myself that we are all capable of breaking free from limitations. Together, we rise, inspire and empower one another. Let’s show up each day with stride, embracing our unique journeys and uplifting those around us. 

Join me in celebrating the strength, resilience, and limitless spirit of women everywhere. 
Together, we are unstoppable! 💪💖

#WomensDay #Limitless #YogaAsTherapy #breakingbarriers #EmpowerWomen #kicachica #yogateacher #mentalhealth

latestPosts.caption:
𝐄𝐯𝐥𝐯𝐞 𝐒𝐭𝐮𝐝𝐢𝐨 (pronounced 𝘌𝘷𝘰𝘭𝘷𝘦)- is an ode to my learnings and experiences turned to reality, & honestly, one of the most exciting things I’ve ever done.⁣
⁣
After teaching movement for over a decade, every time I think I know enough…the more I teach, the more I realize I’m just getting started.⁣
⁣
Here’s what I’ve learned and a sneak peek to the ideology behind my work:⁣
⁣
	•	𝐌𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭 𝐢𝐬 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐛𝐞𝐬𝐭 (𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐞𝐚𝐬𝐢𝐞𝐬𝐭) 𝐟𝐨𝐫𝐦 𝐨𝐟 𝐭𝐡𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐩𝐲.⁣
	•	𝐀𝐥𝐰𝐚𝐲𝐬 𝐜𝐫𝐨𝐬𝐬-𝐭𝐫𝐚𝐢𝐧. Skipping out on mobility, strength, flexibility, agility, or balance? Your body deserves better.⁣
	•	𝐂𝐨𝐧𝐭𝐫𝐨𝐥 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐛𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐡, 𝐜𝐨𝐧𝐭𝐫𝐨𝐥 𝐲𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐞𝐦𝐨𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐬. It’s that simple.⁣
	•	𝐃𝐢𝐬𝐜𝐢𝐩𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐞 𝐢𝐬 𝐞𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐧𝐠. Do it consistently enough, and it stops feeling like work—that’s when real change happens.⁣
⁣
Growth happens outside your comfort zone—so step out, move & become the best version of yourself.⁣
⁣
𝐃𝐨𝐧’𝐭 𝐬𝐭𝐨𝐩, 𝐄𝐕𝐋𝐕𝐄.⁣
⁣
